rComments: Enjoyed her class. Gives a lot of opportunities for extra credit.  A lot of readings, but skim, and you'll be alright. Lecture slides are uploaded but most of the information you need is in lecture. Over time you'll realize she cares but won't put up with crap. Just don't be late for class, and participate a bit in class and she'll love you.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'EXTRA CREDIT', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Caskey is one of the best profs I had in my first year at uni, right up there with Bernice Iarocci. She assigns lots of reading, but tbh you can skim through it and get the idea. It was very discussion based in class and she makes the readings make sense, so even if you didn't read them you're ok. Really funny and inclusive.

I love her! I took FAH267. Her lectures are great, I had to pay attention the entire lecture so I wouldn't miss anything. I understood history from the Roman Empire to the Renaissance. Tests/exams are not easy though.
wonderful professor, wish there were more like her
She's great prof,she's funny too!Love those video clips!

What you wrote is very true, she IS kind! At the same time a extremely talented lecturer, and quite attractive too. assignment/tests are hard, but She gave detailed feedback on essays, very encouraging. I really wished she taught other 3rd year courses. The only setback is the Department's writing initiative and I hope this abolished sometime soon

She's amazing! I highly recommend taking her class. Very nice and approachable and a a fair marker. The assignments are pretty easy although the final exam was very hard. She is very clear and very helpful!

I love Prof. Caskey! She's really nice, very approachable and cristal clear. The material is slightly hard becuase it has alot of Islamic names and stuff that are hard to pronounce let alone spell but she makes it easier. The exam was very hard. She is not a hard marker, very fair. Highly recommended!
